cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a deep learning tool for classifying logistic vehicles in urban areas using images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves the development of an architecture for creating an annotated database and a classifier, which are both machine learning tasks falling under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of traffic counting as a tool for intelligent city planning, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of classical methods for vehicle counting, which could fall under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it involves the security of traffic monitoring systems.
